body:
@marcphilipp awesome, thanks for help! I will try to squash my non-functional commit into yours so we merge only working commits into the main history.

What i was thinking is: Now that the restoring of file & folder permissions will done *before* `deleteAndContinue` is called, the whole `makeWritableAndTryToDeleteAgain` thing introduced in ee5c45f4 become superfluous, correct? The only change that i'd see worth keeping is catching any exceptions around `Files.delete(path);` and adding them to the failures list.

If you agree i would also craft a cleanup commit on top ‚Äì technically the tests introduced for #2046 should warn us anyway providing there is also a windows vm running the ci pipelines.
